question.Q: See a doctor immediately. You may have PNEUMONIA or ACUTE BRONCHITIS especially if you are coughing up mucus that is rusty brown or streaked with red.
Are you short of breath and unable to lie flat on your back, even though you have not been exercising?
Are you coughing up mucus that is pink and frothy?
EMERGENCY Get medical help now! Call 123 or your local emergency number or have someone take you to the nearest hospital emergency department. You may have CONGESTIVE HEART.
Have you recently had surgery, been confined to bed, or sat for prolonged periods during a trip?

EMERGENCY Get medical help now! Call 123 or your local emergency number or have someone take you to the nearest hospital emergency department. You may have a blood clot in your lung. Would you like to continue diagnosis?
Have you had a cold or the flu within the past month that has left you with a persistent cough?
See your doctor. Coughing may have ruptured a small blood vessel in your airway.
Have you had a cough for many weeks or months?
See a doctor immediately. You could have LUNC CANCER or TUBERCULOSIS.
See a doctor immediately if you are unable to make a diagnosis from this chat.
